hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: Could you tell me the number for ? betnovate medscape Contemporary bag-in-box doesn’t need to be about low prices. More about choice, freedom (as we become more health-conscious about galumphing through a whole bottle) and style. We have ice makers in our fridges, watch TV on demand, buy clothes in a click from the kitchen table – why can’t I have three litres of something cold, delicious and dry (picpoul; Australian riesling; gavi; chablis; pale pink from Provence) sitting in my fridge in a smart, ergonomic flat-pack that will be good for three to four weeks? Then I can choose to pour a single glass rather than wrangle with myself about whether it’s worth opening a bottle, or siphon some into a gleaming glass carafe to pour at table for friends who might rapidly move onto red. Or stop drinking. Or not.
